{
  "name": "Hammer of Thunderbolts",
  "type": "weapon",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.</p>\n<p><strong>Giant's Bane (Requires Attunement).</strong> You must be wearing a <strong>belt of &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} &amp;Reference[str]{strength}</strong> (any variety) and <strong>gauntlets of ogre power</strong> to attune to this weapon. The attunement ends if you take off either of those items. While you are attuned to this weapon and holding it, your &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} score increases by 4 and can exceed 20, but not 30. When you roll a 20 on an attack roll made with this weapon against a &amp;Reference[giant]{giant}, the &amp;Reference[giant]{giant} must succeed on a [[/save con 17 format=long]] or die.</p>\n<p>The hammer also has 5 charges. While attuned to it, you can expend 1 charge and make a ranged weapon attack with the hammer, hurling it as if it had the thrown property with a normal range of 20 feet and a long range of 60 feet. If the attack hits, the hammer unleashes a thunderclap audible out to 300 feet. The target and every creature within 30 feet of it must succeed on a [[/save con 17 format=long]] or be &amp;Reference[stunned]{stunned} until the end of your next turn. The hammer regains 1d4 + 1 expended charges daily at dawn.</p>\n</div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
